HEADWORD: algaroth
<hw>al"ga*roth</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l"g⟦adot⟧*r⟦ocr⟧th)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>algaroth</ets>, fr. the name of the
inventor, <persfn><etsep>Algarotti</etsep></persfn>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A term used for the <altname>Powder of
Algaroth</altname>, a white powder which is a compound of trichloride
and trioxide of antimony. It was formerly used in medicine as an emetic,
purgative, and diaphoretic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

